column16: The Instrument of Accession is an agreement signed by the rulers of the various princely state which acceeded to the Dominion of India after independence. This is an agreement signed by the ruler of Alwar, His Highness Shri Sewai Maharaj Tejsinghji Alwarendra Dev making an acceptance of all the clauses and vesting all the powers of the State in the hands of the Dominion of India according to the the Government of India Act, 1935 . It includes an agreement stating the formation of laws recommended by the Dominion Legislature in the fields of defence, external affairs, communications and ancillary related to the State after its accession. A reference to the Indian Arbitration Act, 1899 has also been included in the agreement if in case of any dispute that arises out of the overall agreement.
column24: Shri Sewai Maharaj Tejsinghji Alwarendra Dev
